Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.71,0:03:13.58,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Our organization oversees every industry in Naples.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:16.67,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Passione... That's what we call ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:21.88,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The name Passione comes from \N the word "passion", not the boss's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:26.60,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,No one knows the boss's name, \N or even what he looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.06,0:03:30.39,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We receive orders from \N a number of his capos.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:35.57,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno, the capo who will decide whether you \N join the organization or not is a man named Polpo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.36,0:03:39.44,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He's in this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.65,0:03:41.95,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,But this is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.28,0:03:44.91,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's a prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:50.50,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Correct. Polpo was convicted of an undisclosed crime \N and won't be released for fifteen years. {"Okay, he pretty much devoured everything within a five-block radius of our hideout."}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.50,0:03:55.38,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,However, he still gives out orders from within these walls, \N exercising his power within the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.84,0:04:00.80,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He could leave this place any time, \N but he chooses to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.80,0:04:02.72,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He feels no need to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.72,0:04:03.76,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:05.39,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You'll see for yourself. {here beginneth the fat jokes}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.39,0:04:11.14,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno Giovanna, \N you'll have to pass an interview with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.14,0:04:13.48,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Think of it like any other job interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:16.40,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What the interview will entail \N entirely depends on his mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.40,0:04:19.48,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But whatever you do, \N do not let him discover your true intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:22.07,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.57,0:04:26.32,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. Your Stand ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.32,0:04:27.74,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,That's what you called it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.74,0:04:33.79,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I was going to ask how you got your ability, \N but instead could you tell me if there are others like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.79,0:04:35.96,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That, too, is something \N you'll see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.33,0:04:38.00,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If you pass, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.05,0:04:46.68,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Before entering, please place your watch, \N valuables, and the contents of your pockets in the tray...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.68,0:04:49.68,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,...then proceed to the \N next room for a pat down. {rather a "feel up" *winkwink*}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:08.62,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Stand here, hands raised above your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.95,0:05:14.71,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Once past the gate, \N please continue straight down the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:19.09,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Polpo is in cell N-28.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:23.67,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,The room is divided by a pane of tempered glass, \N but you may {The Japanese phrasing specifically implies that she means that it is possible to talk to him despite the glass pane. It CAN also be taken as "You're allowed to talk to him" though... I'd say phrasing it like this is the best option as it covers both. -Starfish}speak with him. {yeah, this phrasing works -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:29.76,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Touching the glass or exchanging items with him{Technically she says "giving him things and also receiving things from him", but... eh. "Exchanging items" does cover both of those. -Starfish} \N are both strictly forbidden, however.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.51,0:05:32.68,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,You have fifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.23,0:05:37.90,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Once you pass through, \N the gate will close.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.90,0:05:39.98,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Yell for us if anything happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.98,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm going to meet him \N directly in his cell?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.98,0:05:44.44,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Not in a visiting room?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:48.16,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Do you not know who he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.56,0:06:18.60,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,That left arm of yours... {satan-sama, is that you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:20.56,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Is it injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.07,0:06:30.66,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,That's not a bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:39.92,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,I see the fingers on your right hand are slightly reddened, \N as if you've been holding something. {POL POL}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.92,0:06:42.59,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,A bag, judging from the lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.59,0:06:47.67,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,That tells me you've only been using your \N right hand to hold the bag until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.67,0:06:49.59,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.59,0:06:52.64,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Well, uh... You're correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.64,0:06:57.85,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I was holding a bag in my right hand since, \N as you pointed out, I injured my left arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.48,0:07:05.40,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,I envy your freedom to be \N so reckless with your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:09.40,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Care for some wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.95,0:07:12.57,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,I have some exquisite Chianti Classico. {for the record, I've never developed a taste for the stuff, though I probably just haven't had it with the right food as he suggests -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.57,0:07:18.33,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,It pairs perfectly with Scamorza cheese \N and caviar spread over crackers. {I like this, both for how Josh rendered it and the idea -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.33,0:07:23.54,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I was told we weren't \N allowed to exchange items.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.04,0:07:26.84,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,They're all talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.84,0:07:31.01,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,The things people {\i1}say{\i0} \N and the things people {\i1}do{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.01,0:07:35.89,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...are at constant odds. {Brick, where'd you get a hand grenade?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.89,0:07:40.31,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,It's both the best and \N worst aspect of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.31,0:07:45.90,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,The only downside to \N remaining in this cell is, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.69,0:07:47.78,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Polpo...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.69,0:07:51.86,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,{\an8}...the fact that I can no longer admire \N the great work of Michelangelo in the Sistine Chapel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.94,0:07:51.86,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's not that he feels no need to leave prison...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.86,0:07:54.49,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's that nothing would change \N whether he left or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.16,0:07:59.58,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,With a body like that, \N he may even be safer in a cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.91,0:08:04.58,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,The more important question is \N how he even managed to get through the door... {FAT JOKE}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.58,0:08:07.67,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Buccellati spoke with me about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.55,0:08:12.26,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,So you'd like to join our organization, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.26,0:08:15.34,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Hmm... Giorno Giovanna, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.59,0:08:20.68,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Anyway, why don't we get \N this interview underway?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.45,0:08:40.24,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:41.62,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Were my eyes deceiving me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.62,0:08:45.83,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,For a second, it looked like Polpo took \N a bite out of his fingers with the cracker... {Tasty}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:51.88,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,No... Perhaps Polpo is just \N a Stand user like Buccellati. {he got the shoku shoku no mi, can turn anything edible}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.76,0:08:57.34,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Either way, I have to make sure \N he doesn't find out that I'm one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.34,0:09:05.77,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,What do you believe is the most important quality \N that a potential candidate could possess, Giorno Giovanna?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.90,0:09:09.65,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Perhaps how capable they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.65,0:09:13.53,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Oh? So just how capable are {\i1}you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:21.62,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,During my pat down, \N I borrowed these from that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:25.08,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I thought they may prove \N useful for your test.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:27.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'll return them to her \N when I leave, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.96,0:09:33.76,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,What else can you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:40.55,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Besides that, the only other unique skill I have \N is being able to stuff my ear inside my ear canal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:46.06,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Now {\i1}that's{\i0} an amusing skill!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.10,0:09:48.06,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,But, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.06,0:09:52.82,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,The most important quality one can possess \N is something else entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.82,0:09:57.53,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,It's trustworthiness, \N Giorno Giovanna, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.53,0:10:02.79,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,The most important quality a candidate \N can possess is trustworthiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.79,0:10:11.13,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Being clever or talented are worth as much as \N the piece of cracker stuck between my teeth in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.75,0:10:16.97,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,This test will evaluate your trustworthiness...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.97,0:10:19.93,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...through the flame of this lighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:27.31,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Take it with you and ensure \N the flame is never extinguished.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.27,0:10:31.65,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.65,0:10:34.48,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Take extra precautions to ensure \N the flame isn't disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.82,0:10:38.45,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,A 17th-century theologian \N by the name of Fuller once said...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.45,0:10:43.83,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,"He's my friend that speaks \N well of me behind my back." {This is an exact quote from Thomas Fuller, so don't change this under any circumstances. -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:50.79,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,In order to join our organization, you'll have to demonstrate \N your trustworthiness even when you aren't being watched.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.79,0:10:57.26,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Your task is to keep this lighter for twenty-four hours \N without letting the flame go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:02.76,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Manage that, and you may enter our ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:04.26,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Simple, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:07.10,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,The lighter has plenty of fluid in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.10,0:11:13.56,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,All you have to do is sit quietly in your room \N and watch over the flame until 3:00 PM tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.56,0:11:19.53,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,If you're a diligent man and act carefully, \N the flame should never go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.53,0:11:23.12,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Ergo, we'll be able to trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.12,0:11:29.21,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,However, if you're a man \N who would take me lightly...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.21,0:11:36.71,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...and end up falling asleep, sneezing, knocking over the lighter, \N or letting a gust of wind blow out the flame...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:45.01,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,...that would mean you're untrustworthy, \N and therefore unworthy to join our organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:48.68,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,Now, take the lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.97,0:11:51.89,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,This is your entrance exam. {imagine college entrance exams like this}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.15,0:12:01.74,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,You have twenty-four hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.07,0:12:08.62,Main,Polpo,0,0,0,,I look forward to seeing you again \N at 3:00 PM tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.62,0:12:10.33,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Twenty-four hours...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:14.58,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,All visitors are to be subjected to another pat down \N upon passing through the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.21,0:12:20.51,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,Once you've received permission \N to leave the facility...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.51,0:12:24.05,Main,Cop,0,0,0,,...continue to the next room \N to reclaim your belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:27.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Wait! \N Polpo didn't explain anything to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:28.60,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.43,0:12:31.98,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Get in position \N for your pat down!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:36.48,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,You were warned that accepting \N anything from him was strictly forbidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.48,0:12:42.57,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,This is bad! I had the impression that Polpo was \N bribing these people to allow me to leave with the lighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.57,0:12:46.20,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Visitor, raise your hands \N and proceed forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.20,0:12:50.16,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,So Polpo's test has already begun...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.16,0:12:51.20,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.20,0:12:53.08,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,...can't fail here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.08,0:12:58.71,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I need to pass this test \N and become a member of Passione!
Comment: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:01.01,Main,,0,0,0,,C {Shifted FORWARD 23 frames}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.38,0:13:07.34,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Step forward, visitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.34,0:13:11.68,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Just like I hid her ID in my hand \N where no one could see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:12.68,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,{\an8}Raise your hands and proceed forward! \N Prepare for your pat down!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.14,0:13:13.64,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,...I'll hide this flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.21,0:13:45.92,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,You're free to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.92,0:13:47.72,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Nothing seems to be amiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.09,0:13:50.22,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,You may leave the facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.22,0:13:50.89,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:54.27,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Please open your hands \N and display your palms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.27,0:13:59.52,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,I'll remind you again that \N accepting anything from him is strictly forbidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.52,0:14:03.36,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Open your hands, visitor! \N I'm checking them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.08,0:14:17.29,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,A flower?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.96,0:14:22.09,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,A real flower?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.67,0:14:26.88,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,Fine. I see no reason not to allow this. {You don't know the kind of stuff you could smuggle inside a flower, such as... idk, one of the 72 sterling silver Krana-Kal, maybe. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:29.05,Main,Cop Lady,0,0,0,,You may now leave the facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:41.19,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I turned the lighter into a flower \N and hid the flame within its petals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.77,0:14:43.48,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,That was too close...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.90,0:14:48.99,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,But could this flame be \N Polpo's Stand ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.04,0:15:02.00,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,This wind could ruin everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:04.17,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Hey, Giorno! Perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.17,0:15:07.13,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,Could you push the shutter \N button on the camera for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.13,0:15:08.22,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.68,0:15:13.64,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you, \N but could you help me carry this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:14.30,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.15,0:15:25.77,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I finally made it back to my dorm...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.45,0:15:34.37,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Th-That was close...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:49.26,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This should stop the lighter from falling over, \N and these objects will protect it from any air currents.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.26,0:15:56.93,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I just need to keep a close eye on it for the next \N twenty-three hours until I see Polpo at 3:00 PM tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.93,0:15:58.18,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.18,0:16:01.23,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'll make sure my \N window is locked, just in case...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:04.98,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I don't want it opening \N and letting any gusts of wind in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.28,0:16:10.82,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.82,0:16:12.99,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Who could be opening my door \N without knocking first?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:16.74,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Th-That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.58,0:16:21.41,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Looks like he's out...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.91,0:16:23.62,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Now's my chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:25.54,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's that Japanese guy again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.54,0:16:28.13,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, \N his name is Koichi Hirose! {Do NOT change this to Hirose Koichi. He says his name in western order and we're leaving it that way. -J} {BUT MUH JAPUHNEESES}{HUSH YOU} {lol}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.42,0:16:31.22,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,How did he know where I live?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.97,0:16:36.43,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Guess my suitcase and \N belongings are gone by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.43,0:16:40.77,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,But maybe my passport \N is lying around here somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.77,0:16:45.35,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I bet selling someone's ID \N would be really tough...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.35,0:16:49.86,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I kinda feel like a burglar \N sneaking into his room like this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:52.15,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,No! {\i1}He's{\i0} the thief here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.15,0:16:54.82,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,What's so wrong with taking my stuff back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.82,0:16:57.07,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,His passport? No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.53,0:17:00.24,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's in the file box on top of my desk!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.24,0:17:02.04,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I was planning on returning it to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.04,0:17:05.54,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Soon Koichi will notice the lighter's flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.54,0:17:08.46,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,If he does, he'll probably put it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.46,0:17:10.30,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,He won't want to risk starting a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:12.80,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,What should I do? What should I {\i1}do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:16.55,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I need to get the lighter back{as in, he needs to keep it with himself rather than letting Koichi take it and put it out. -Starfish} \N as soon as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.01,0:17:20.18,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Gold Experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:35.24,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I used Gold Experience to imbue \N the lamp's cord with the life of a snake.{YOU DON'T SAY. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.24,0:17:37.61,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,That bread is quite tasty, after all.{Perhaps just a personal thing, but yeah... PERSONALLY I was never much fond of the specific addition that the lampsnake would want to eat the bread. It kinda goes without saying. As, indeed... the JP doesn't say it. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.61,0:17:38.95,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,It went for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.53,0:17:41.33,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Now to pull it up with the cord...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:43.91,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,What happened? \N It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.79,0:17:51.13,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.13,0:17:53.38,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,He found the lighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.38,0:17:54.76,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,This won't end well!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.17,0:17:57.80,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,I need to make sure \N he won't put out the flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.89,0:18:05.52,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,This symbol! \N It's the official seal of Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.52,0:18:08.98,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I found it! My passport!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.06,0:18:12.11,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,I-It's burning! {found our next emoji}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.49,0:18:17.11,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Thank goodness...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.99,0:18:18.95,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.95,0:18:22.91,Main,Koichi,0,0,0,,That's strange... \N I swear I saw a lit lighter... {Koichi after all the shit you've been through, you really shouldn't be so nonchalant about a magical disappearing lighter. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.41,0:18:25.58,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What a close call...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.20,0:18:28.96,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,He nearly extinguished the flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.58,0:18:32.34,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I, Giorno Giovanna, have a dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.34,0:18:37.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,In order to take my first step toward achieving that dream, \N I must protect this flame at all costs! {RIP the dream}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.01,0:18:42.64,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Whoops, almost got ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.64,0:18:46.43,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Real sorry about that! \N I was cleaning the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.43,0:18:51.61,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Oh, you were just splashed a bit. \N I'm happy you weren't soaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.61,0:18:56.23,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Perhaps we're being rewarded\N for our good deeds.{Was: "We must be having good luck \N for the kind deeds we've done." This could definitely be seen as overstepping this late in the process so revert if you feel it absolutely is not okay but I REALLY did not like the previous phrasing. -Starfish OF FINAL QC}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.49,0:18:59.20,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Doing good deeds is very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:05.83,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,If you had been acting unkind, I probably \N would have gotten you with the whole bucket of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.83,0:19:08.96,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No way... \N This can't be happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.37,0:19:10.50,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The flame...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:15.13,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,If I ask, will Polpo let me try again?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.71,0:19:17.05,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.05,0:19:21.64,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,If he were that forgiving, \N he wouldn't have given me a test like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.64,0:19:23.10,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Flame?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.10,0:19:27.06,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Is your lighter not working anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.06,0:19:30.56,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Is it ruined? \N Was that my fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.56,0:19:33.19,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No, it wasn't you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:35.94,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I just need to figure out \N what I'm going to do about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.94,0:19:40.40,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Far as I can see, \N it doesn't look damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:44.24,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,It's still letting out gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.24,0:19:46.79,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:52.71,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Yeah, gas is still coming out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.71,0:19:54.71,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Is this the flint?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.71,0:19:56.59,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,Did you try pushing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.59,0:20:00.76,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,That's impossible... \N It shouldn't be possible to reignite it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.05,0:20:02.84,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,{\an8}Just look at this fine craftsmanship!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.38,0:20:04.43,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,This entire test was predicated on \N whether or not the flame stayed lit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.84,0:20:05.68,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,{\an8}Such an impressive lighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.76,0:20:08.39,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If I were able to reignite it, \N this test would be pointless!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.23,0:20:18.11,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,It was shockingly bright for a second there, \N but it seems to be working.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.11,0:20:18.94,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.94,0:20:25.70,Main,OLD MAN,0,0,0,,By the way, you wouldn't happen to be using that lighter \N to light cigarettes, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:27.41,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,This isn't right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.41,0:20:30.58,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,It actually lit up again... \N Something is wrong here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.46,0:20:41.97,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Is that a...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.97,0:20:44.43,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Could that really be a Sta{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.43,0:20:47.64,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,You reignited the lighter, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.64,0:20:52.23,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,You shall be given one chance. \N Two paths lie before you. {This is the same as line 277}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.23,0:20:53.69,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Th-That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:57.52,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,The first path leads to the life of a chosen one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.52,0:21:00.73,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,The other leads to your demise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.73,0:21:02.40,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,A Stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.40,0:21:04.99,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,That must be Polpo's Stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.99,0:21:06.24,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.24,0:21:08.83,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,You reignited the lighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.20,0:21:11.20,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,Accept your fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.87,0:21:16.08,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It can't be! You villain! \N What are you doing?!{He's specifically addressing Black Sabbath here. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:22.09,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,This soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.84,0:21:26.55,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,...was not one worthy of being chosen. {Bullshit, this guy definitely had big Stand energy. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.55,0:21:28.72,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,"Worthy of being chosen"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.06,0:21:33.68,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,H-Hey, are you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.14,0:21:38.31,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,He's dead... \N Uninjured, but dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.81,0:21:42.03,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Is it because it attacked his soul?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.03,0:21:47.32,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Does his Stand drag out people's souls \N and kill them with an arrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.32,0:21:48.99,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Could that be it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.32,0:21:56.12,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,But what does "worthy of being chosen" mean? \N Someone who can join the gang?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.58,0:21:58.63,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,You, too, reignited the lighter, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.63,0:22:03.55,Main,Black Sabbath,0,0,0,,You shall be given one chance. \N Two paths lie before you. {This is the same as line 257}
